Governor Seyi Makinde, Hon Akeem Ademola Ige, has assured stakeholders in the industry of renewed commitement that will enhance development of the state tourism sector. Hon. Ige said on tourism promotion and developmemt, the present government is poised to transform the sector for economic growth and job creation. He explained that Governor Makinde understands the importance of tourism and has promised that the sector will not suffer neglect under his administration. “Part of his agenda is to diversify into other sectors that can generate income and jobs for our teeming youths and he said agriculture and creative industy and tourism were his target.” He maintained that his office will synergise with stakeholders in the sector to enhance rapid development and economic benefit. “Very soon, we will embark on assessment tour of all the tourism sites in the state to see what we can to do to improve on and bring in private investors for immediate development. He, however, appealed to the stakeholders in the sector to cooperate with the government with a view to creating an enabling environment for their businesses to thrive. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Court Threatens To Revoke Shehu Sani’s Bail The Federal High Court, Abuja, Monday, said it would revoke the bail granted Senator Shehu Sani if he fails to appear in court on the next adjourned date for the trial of the two-count criminal charges preferred against him by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission… Read Full Story Buhari Appoints New Chief Personal Security Officer President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), Aliyu Abubakar Musa, as his Chief Personal Security Officer (CPSO). He replaces Commissioner of Police (CP) Abdulkarim Dauda, who was recently redeployed… Read Full Story APC: Buni-Led Caretaker Committee Promises True Reconciliation As part of measure to make progress on its mandate in reconciling all factions in the ruli